<subSubSection id="BAF265724F3BFF960723FD62FE5B577C" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="1291" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF970723FD62FA9A5265" blockId="22.[827,1443,758,1026]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FD62FC5C5568" box="[827,962,759,780]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin denticulated between exorbital, epibranchial teeth. Cheliped carpus inner margin with two large subequal pointed teeth; cheliped carpus outer margin with two or three teeth; anterolateral margin of carapace behind epibranchial tooth with several small teeth; carpi, propodi of P2–5 with spines on their margins; margins of meri of P2–5 either smooth or sparsley setose; G1 TA slim tapering, not widened by raised lobes (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF97009CFC79FB6B5265" box="[1156,1269,1004,1026]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="14.[163,241,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,195,1303]" captionTargetId="figure-309@14.[163,1443,195,1303]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 4. Gonopods 1 and 2 of the four genera in Erimetopini. A–C, Erimetopus vandenbrandeni; D–F, Longipotamonautes ballayi; G–I, Nesonautes margaritarius; J–L, Occidensonautes ecorssei. Scale bar: A–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461487/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF970723FBBEFB12523B" blockId="22.[827,1442,1066,1119]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FBBEFC535224" box="[827,973,1067,1088]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<typeStatus id="2D53885B4F3BFF970723FBBEFCEF5224" box="[827,881,1067,1088]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9707F9FBBEFCEC523B" authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1886" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1886" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brazzae">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9707F9FBBEFB5B525B" box="[993,1221,1066,1088]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus brazzae</emphasis>
A. 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF9700F4FBBFFCEC523B" author="Milne-Edwards A" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="148 - 151" refId="ref34887" refString="Milne-Edwards A. 1886. La description de quelques crustaces du genre Thelphusa recueillis par M. De Brazza dans les regions du Congo. Bulletin de la Societe Philosophique Paris, series 7: 148 - 151." type="book chapter" year="1886">Milne-Edwards, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF970723FB1DFC4A52BF" blockId="22.[827,1443,1160,1243]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FB1DFA8752F9" box="[827,1305,1160,1181]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
Species included: 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF97003AFB1DFA8752F9" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1886" box="[1058,1305,1160,1181]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brazzae">Erimetopus brazzae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(A. Milne- Edwards, 1886) and 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970058FB32FC5152BF" authority="(Balss, 1936)" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Balss" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vandenbrandeni">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970058FB32FA3D52DF" box="[1088,1443,1190,1212]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus vandenbrandeni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF97075BFB50FC5A52BF" author="Balss H" box="[835,964,1221,1243]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="165 - 204" refId="ref29128" refString="Balss H. 1936. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Potamonidae (Susswasserkrabben) des Kongogebietes. Revue Zoologique et Botanique d'Afrique 28: 165 - 204." type="journal article" year="1936">Balss, 1936</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF970723FA91FC0653F0" blockId="22.[827,1444,1284,1428]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FA91FAC6537D" box="[827,1368,1284,1305]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
Distribution: 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970030FA91FAC6537D" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1886" box="[1064,1368,1284,1305]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brazzae">Erimetopus brazzae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970723FAB6FB935353" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Balss" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[827,1037,1314,1336]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vandenbrandeni">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FAB6FB935353" box="[827,1037,1314,1336]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">E.vandenbrandeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are endemic to the Lower and Middle CongoRiverBasinintheRepublicoftheCongoandtheD.R. 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970723FAF5FC1F5311" box="[827,897,1376,1397]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
(Cumberlidge, 1999; 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF970077FAF5FA035311" author="Cumberlidge N &amp; Reed SK" box="[1135,1437,1376,1398]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref32419" refString="Cumberlidge N, Reed SK. 2004. Erimetopus vandenbrandeni (Balss, 1936) comb. nov., with notes on the taxonomy of the genus Erimetopus Rathbun, 1894 (Brachyura: Potamoidea: Potamonautidae) from Central Africa. Zootaxa 422: 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2004">Cumberlidge &amp; Reed, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF970723FAEBFC1453F0" box="[827,906,1406,1428]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="18.[163,241,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-252@18.[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 9. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the four genera of Erimetopini (A) Erimetopus, (B) Longipotamonautes, (C) Nesonautes and (D) Occidensonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF960723FA28FE5B577C" blockId="22.[827,1443,1469,1890]" lastBlockId="23.[145,761,197,280]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="1291" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FA28FBAB53B7" box="[827,1077,1469,1491]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9707AAFA2BFBAB53B7" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[946,1077,1470,1491]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Erimetopus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is revised and redescribed here. 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970723FA49FC585395" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[827,966,1500,1521]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723FA49FC585395" box="[827,966,1500,1521]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accommodates two species of unusual freshwater crabs from the 
<collectingRegion id="302CF81B4F3BFF970095FA6EFAB15074" box="[1165,1327,1531,1552]" country="Republic of the Congo" name="Bas-Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Lower Congo</collectingRegion>
Basin in Central Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF97001AF98CFACD504A" author="Cumberlidge N &amp; Reed SK" box="[1026,1363,1561,1583]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref32419" refString="Cumberlidge N, Reed SK. 2004. Erimetopus vandenbrandeni (Balss, 1936) comb. nov., with notes on the taxonomy of the genus Erimetopus Rathbun, 1894 (Brachyura: Potamoidea: Potamonautidae) from Central Africa. Zootaxa 422: 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2004">Cumberlidge &amp; Reed, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF970176F98FFC1A502A" author="Bott R" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="209 - 352" refId="ref29250" refString="Bott R. 1955. Die Susswasserkrabben von Africa und ihre Stammesgeschichte. Annales du Musee Royal du Congo Belge serie 3: 209 - 352." type="journal article" year="1955">Bott (1955)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970005F9ADFAFA5029" authority="" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1955" box="[1053,1380,1592,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Potamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Erimetopus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970005F9ADFB5C5029" box="[1053,1218,1592,1613]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Potamonautes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9700CCF9ADFAC25029" box="[1236,1372,1592,1613]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970723F9C2FB535008" authority="Rathbun, 1894" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[827,1229,1622,1644]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723F9C2FBBC5008" box="[827,1058,1623,1644]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus spinosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF970030F9C3FB535008" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[1064,1229,1622,1644]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="25 - 27" refId="ref36341" refString="Rathbun MJ. 1894. Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of African fresh-water crabs. Proceedings of the U. S. National Museum 17: 25 - 27." type="journal article" year="1894">Rathbun, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="2D53885B4F3BFF970105F9C2FAD05008" box="[1309,1358,1623,1644]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">type</typeStatus>
species for two species, 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9707E1F9E3FC0750CD" authority="brazzae" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Potamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brazzae" subGenus="Erimetopus" subSpecies="brazzae">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9707E1F9E3FC0750CD" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Potamonautes (Erimetopus) brazzae brazzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9707C6F901FC7150A3" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9707C6F901FC7250A3" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1955" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Potamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brazzae" subGenus="Erimetopus" subSpecies="frontospinulosa">Potamonautes (Erimetopus) brazzae frontospinulosa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF9707EBF927FAB850AD" author="Cumberlidge N &amp; Reed SK" box="[1011,1318,1714,1737]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref32419" refString="Cumberlidge N, Reed SK. 2004. Erimetopus vandenbrandeni (Balss, 1936) comb. nov., with notes on the taxonomy of the genus Erimetopus Rathbun, 1894 (Brachyura: Potamoidea: Potamonautidae) from Central Africa. Zootaxa 422: 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2004">Cumberlidge &amp; Reed (2004)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970723F947FC225083" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[827,956,1746,1767]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723F947FC225083" box="[827,956,1746,1767]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus with two species, 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970129F947FA3C5082" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1955" box="[1329,1442,1745,1767]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Potamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brazzae">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970129F947FA3C5082" box="[1329,1442,1745,1767]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">E. brazzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970771F965FBA25161" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Balss" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[873,1084,1776,1797]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vandenbrandeni">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970771F965FCE55161" box="[873,891,1776,1797]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF97079DF965FBA25161" box="[901,1084,1776,1797]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">vandenbrandeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The phylogenies of 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF97010DF965FCE45140" author="Daniels SR &amp; Phiri EE &amp; Klaus S &amp; Albrecht C &amp; Cumberlidge N" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="549 - 567" refId="ref33273" refString="Daniels SR, Phiri EE, Klaus S, Albrecht C, Cumberlidge N. 2015. Multi-locus phylogeny of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna reveals historical drainage connectivity and transoceanic dispersal since the Eocene. Systematic Biology 64: 549 - 567." type="journal article" year="2015">
Daniels 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970177F965FA3D5161" box="[1391,1443,1776,1797]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">et al.</emphasis>
(2015
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2), 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF9707C0F89BFB7E5147" author="Daniels SR &amp; Klaus S" box="[984,1248,1806,1828]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="119 - 128" refId="ref33119" refString="Daniels SR, Klaus S. 2018. Divergent evolutionary origins and biogeographic histories of two freshwater crabs (Brachyura: Potamonautes) on the West African conveyer belt islands of Sao Tome and Principe. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 127: 119 - 128." type="journal article" year="2018">Daniels &amp; Klaus (2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig 1) and 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF97017DF89BFC255126" author="Wood LE &amp; De Grave S &amp; Cumberlidge N &amp; Kennerley A &amp; Daniels SR" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="2219 - 2230" refId="ref37030" refString="Wood LE, De Grave S, Cumberlidge N, Kennerley A, Daniels SR. 2019. A phylogenetic perspective on biodiversity patterns of Afrotropical freshwater crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Potamonautidae). Aquatic Conservation: Marine and Freshwater Ecosystems 29: 2219 - 2230." type="journal article" year="2019">
Wood 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970723F8BBFCEA5126" box="[827,884,1837,1859]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">et al.</emphasis>
(2019
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9707D1F8B8FB945126" box="[969,1034,1837,1859]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[163,244,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[164,1447,197,865]" captionTargetId="figure-453@2.[163,1449,195,866]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. A, maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna based on four DNA loci with support values (posterior probabilities and bootstrap values of the ML analyses) with a geological timescale below the tree topology. Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.95 pP (*above branch) and bootstrap values&gt; 75% (* below branch) were regarded as statistically supported and are shown on the tree topology. Clade A, Liberonautinae, clade B, Potamonautinae, clade B1, Maritimonautini, clade B2, Erimetopini, clade B3, Potamonautini. B, detail of the maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna showing Clade B3 Potamonautini with the species included in the five genera within the tribe: Arcopotamonautes (B3[1]), Lirrangopotamonautes (B3[2]), Platythelphusa (B3[3]), Potamonautes s.s. (B3[4]) and Rotundopotamonautes (B3[5])." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461481/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) all recovered 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9700ADF8BBFAB35126" authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1955" box="[1205,1325,1837,1859]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Potamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brazzae">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9700ADF8BBFAB35126" box="[1205,1325,1837,1859]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">E. brazzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a welldefined lineage sister to 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970046F8D9FA3D5105" box="[1118,1443,1868,1889]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970046F8D9FA025105" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[1118,1436,1868,1889]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Longipotamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ballayi">Longipotamonautes ballayi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The lineage represented by 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3AFF9605C9FF53FF51569D" authority="(Bott, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="Bott" baseAuthorityYear="1955" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Longipotamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3AFF9605C9FF53FD2C56BF" box="[465,690,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291">Longipotamonautes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3AFF9606D9FF53FF59569E" author="Bott R" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291" pagination="209 - 352" refId="ref29250" refString="Bott R. 1955. Die Susswasserkrabben von Africa und ihre Stammesgeschichte. Annales du Musee Royal du Congo Belge serie 3: 209 - 352." type="journal article" year="1955">Bott, 1955</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the branch for 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3AFF9605FFFF71FD67569D" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Marchand" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[487,761,228,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Occidensonautes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecorssei">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3AFF9605FFFF71FD67569D" box="[487,761,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291">Occidensonautes ecorssei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from West Africa (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3AFF960542FE97FE36577C" box="[346,424,258,280]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[163,244,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[164,1447,197,865]" captionTargetId="figure-453@2.[163,1449,195,866]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. A, maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna based on four DNA loci with support values (posterior probabilities and bootstrap values of the ML analyses) with a geological timescale below the tree topology. Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.95 pP (*above branch) and bootstrap values&gt; 75% (* below branch) were regarded as statistically supported and are shown on the tree topology. Clade A, Liberonautinae, clade B, Potamonautinae, clade B1, Maritimonautini, clade B2, Erimetopini, clade B3, Potamonautini. B, detail of the maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna showing Clade B3 Potamonautini with the species included in the five genera within the tribe: Arcopotamonautes (B3[1]), Lirrangopotamonautes (B3[2]), Platythelphusa (B3[3]), Potamonautes s.s. (B3[4]) and Rotundopotamonautes (B3[5])." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461481/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3AFF9605B0FE96FE29577C" box="[424,439,259,280]" captionStart="Figure" captionStartId="11.[145,172,844,866]" captionTargetBox="[149,757,195,804]" captionTargetId="figure-779@11.[149,757,195,804]" captionText="Figure 2. Liberonautinae. Gonopods 1 and 2 of Liberonautes latidactylus, NMU9.V.2005B (CW 72, CL 47.2, CH 20.5, FW 19.3 mm) Guinea, West Africa. A, left G1 ventral view; (B) left G1 dorsal view; (C) left G2 ventral view. Scale bar: A, B = 2.8 mm, C = 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461483/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1291">2</figureCitation>
